It's still unclear what led to the shooting that took place early on Sunday morning. JOHANNESBURG - Two security guards have been wounded in a shooting in City Deep outside Johannesburg.It's still unclear what led to the shooting that took place early on Sunday morning.Paramedics say the men were rushed to hospital in a critical condition.ER24 spokesperson Chitra Bodasing Harduth says: ER24 and other services attended to two security guards who were shot close to a railway line. During assessment it was found that the men were in a critical condition. The men were treated and transported to hospital for further medical care. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)